dct_alternative_sm: North Island New Zealand Showing Land Transactions, 1904-1905
dct_description_sm: By Authority: John Mackay, Government Printer ; Head Office, Department of Lands and Survey, Wellington, N.Z. F.W. Flanagan Chief Draughtsman ; J. W. A. Marchant, Surveyor General.
Table, with dates: "Estates purchased under the land for settlements acts up to 31st March, 1905...The numbers in red correspond with those on the map."
Coloring indicates "Lands taken up during the year," "Lands available for settlement," and "Under Land for Settlements Act."
Shows railroads, roads, cities and towns, waterways, swamps, small islands.
